. Autonomous Robot Economy L1
Overview

Autonomous Robot Economy L1 provides a blockchain infrastructure where robots and machines can transact autonomously for services, resources, and maintenance.

Features

Machine-to-machine payments

Autonomous service contracts

Device identity verification

Resource allocation protocols

Secure machine marketplaces

Architecture
Device Identity Layer

Registers machines with verifiable digital identities.

Smart Contract Economy

Automates service payments and tasks.

Coordination Layer

Enables robots to negotiate services and resources.

Data Exchange Module

Handles secure data communication.

Use Cases

Autonomous delivery networks

Industrial automation markets

Robot service marketplaces

Smart factory coordination
